<h3><center>Another herd <a NAME="slaughtered">slaughtered</a> in France</center></h3>
11 July 96 ... AP
 A herd of 155 cows in the Cantal region of central France was
slaughtered yesterday after one was found to have BSE. The animal was
born in 1991, after the ban on livestock feed imported from Britain came
into effect. It was the ninth case in France this year and the 22nd
since 1990, officials said. <hr>

