colony of marmosets for use in neuropsychological research,  More than
100 born between 1980 and 1990 were fed for their entire lives, 5-10
years, on a diet including pellets containing 20% ruminant-derived
protein (cf about 4% in cattle feed in the same period). None developed spongiform encephalopathy<p>
The authors conclude
"Our observation serves as a reminder that the oral route is probably
an inefficient mode of infection for spongiform encephalopathy across
the species barrier." [Marmosets, a new world monkey, also did not acquire BSE from intra-cranial inoculations -- webmaster]<p>
