following statements on vacas loucas:
<ol><li>In Portugal some cases of BSE  have been detected in cattle imported from
the UK and other EU countries (Netherlands, at least); the first case was
detected in June 1990, the second in February 1991, the third in October
1992. In the three cases, cattle was legally brought by the State to the
owner, then slaughtered and finally the body was cremated and the brain
analysed. It seems that<b> none of these cases have been reported to the
European Commission in the due time</b>. Starting from this date, newspaper
articles become even more confused.<p>

